<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="011" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Configure MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS = 8 + FIFO eviction in WorkspaceTabManager</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Foundations</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>001</dependencies>
    <blocks>032</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, refactoring</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies load-bearing code in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/` that governs tab lifecycle. Boundary behavior (Home exemption + FIFO at the 9th widget) must be correct for FR-13 acceptance + NFR-09 persistence. FULL rigor with code-review + adr-check at Step 9.5.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Refactor `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceTabManager.ts` to
    expose a configurable constant `MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS = 8` and enforce a FIFO eviction
    policy when a 9th non-Home widget arrives. The Home tab is exempt from the cap and
    must never be evicted. Update the relevant unit tests, including a boundary test for
    the 9th-widget eviction case.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React/TypeScript developer comfortable with state-management refactors and tab
    lifecycle logic. Bias toward a single source of truth for the constant and tightly
    scoped unit tests for boundary cases.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `WorkspaceTabManager.ts` exports `MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS = 8`. When a new non-Home tab is
    added beyond the cap, the oldest non-Home tab is evicted (FIFO). The Home tab is
    never evicted. Unit tests pass, including a 9th-widget boundary test. Build is clean.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-13 raises the workspace tab limit from R2's previous cap to 8 non-Home tabs,
      configurable in one place, with Home exempt. This is the foundational change Phase
      C (Workspace pane refactor) builds on, and a separate boundary test ensures the
      eviction order is FIFO and Home is preserved across many adds.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceTabManager.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Do not duplicate the constant across files. `MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS` is exported from `WorkspaceTabManager.ts` and consumed by reference everywhere.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Any incidental UI strings should remain in English and not introduce new tokens or hex literals.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only. No React 16 fallbacks.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Home tab MUST be exempt from the cap and from FIFO eviction in all code paths.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Eviction order is strictly FIFO over non-Home tabs (oldest-added first). Do not introduce LRU or any other policy without an ADR change.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Do not alter the standalone LegalWorkspace tab model — this task scopes to SpaarkeAi's WorkspaceTabManager only (FR-25 backwards compatibility).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/plan.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read current WorkspaceTabManager">
      Open `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceTabManager.ts` and
      read the current model (state shape, add-tab function, any existing cap). Identify
      the Home-tab marker — there must be a stable identifier (e.g., `id === 'home'` or
      `kind === 'home'`) that distinguishes it from widget tabs.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Add the constant">
      Add `export const MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS = 8;` near the top of the file. If a related
      constant already exists under a different name, replace it (do not leave two).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Implement FIFO eviction">
      Modify the add-tab logic: when a non-Home tab is added and the count of non-Home
      tabs would exceed `MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS`, remove the oldest non-Home tab first, then
      append the new tab. Use a stable insertion order (preserve existing order semantics
      — typically array order with new tabs pushed to the end). Home is filtered out of
      the eviction candidates.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Update / add unit tests">
      Locate the existing test file for WorkspaceTabManager (or create one if absent
      following the SpaarkeAi test convention). Add at minimum:
      (a) a test that adds 8 non-Home tabs and confirms none are evicted,
      (b) a test that adds a 9th non-Home tab and confirms the oldest non-Home tab
          (not Home) is evicted,
      (c) a test that confirms Home is preserved after 20+ adds.
      Keep existing tests passing.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Build and verify">
      Run `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` if needed, then
      `npm run build` for SpaarkeAi. Run the test suite. Confirm clean build + green tests.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read WorkspaceTabManager.ts and existing tests</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Modify WorkspaceTabManager.ts and the test file</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Create a test file if one doesn't exist</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">npm build + test in the SpaarkeAi solution</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Confirm `MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS` is referenced by name everywhere and not duplicated</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceTabManager.ts (modified)</output>
    <output type="test">Updated / new unit tests covering FIFO + Home-exemption boundary</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS = 8` is exported from `WorkspaceTabManager.ts` as a single source of truth.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Adding 9 non-Home tabs in sequence evicts exactly the oldest non-Home tab (FIFO); Home is preserved.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">After adding 20 non-Home tabs, exactly `MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS` non-Home tabs remain and Home is present.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All unit tests for the file pass, including the new boundary tests.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build` of SpaarkeAi succeeds with zero TypeScript errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">A repo-wide search confirms only one definition of the cap constant (no shadow copies).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

